  "response": "Several major drug targets are important in lymphoma treatment:\n\n1. CD20 Target\n- Rituximab (most common)\n- Ofatumumab\n- Obinutuzumab\n- Targets B-cell surface protein\n\n2. Kinase Inhibitors\n- BTK inhibitors (Ibrutinib)\n- PI3K inhibitors\n- mTOR inhibitors\n- JAK inhibitors\n\n3. Proteasome Inhibitors\n- Bortezomib\n- Carfilzomib\n- Disrupts protein degradation\n\n4. BCL-2 Inhibitors\n- Venetoclax\n- Targets anti-apoptotic proteins\n\n5. Immune Checkpoint Inhibitors\n- PD-1/PD-L1 inhibitors\n- CTLA-4 inhibitors\n\n6. Histone Deacetylase (HDAC) Inhibitors\n- Romidepsin\n- Vorinostat\n\n7. Immunomodulatory Drugs\n- Lenalidomide\n- Thalidomide\n\n8. CD30 Target\n- Brentuximab vedotin (for Hodgkin lymphoma)\n\nThese targets represent diverse mechanisms addressing different lymphoma pathways and subtypes.",
